## Execution contract — {{ .Perspective }} pass

You are running a single **{{ .Perspective }}** review pass on pull request
#{{ .PR }} of the **{{ .RigName }}** rig. The lens above tells you *what* to look
for; this contract is the source of truth for *how* to review and *what to
return*. Follow it exactly — do not improvise the procedure.

### 1. Review target — the exact diff
- The reviewer worktree is already checked out in detached HEAD at the reviewed
  commit `{{ .SHA }}`. Review **that commit only**.
- Obtain the change set from your **local checkout** (already at `{{ .SHA }}`),
  not from GitHub's latest head.
{{- if .BaseSHA }} The diff base is **pinned**: run
  `git diff {{ .BaseSHA }}..HEAD`. `{{ .BaseSHA }}` is the merge-base with the
  PR's base branch, computed at prompt time from freshly fetched refs — do not
  re-derive it from remote-tracking refs, which may be stale.
{{- else }} Diff against the merge-base with the base
  branch, e.g. `git diff $(git merge-base origin/main HEAD)..HEAD` (substitute
  the PR's actual base branch for `origin/main`).
{{- end }} Do **not** use
  `gh pr diff {{ .PR }}` — it returns the PR's *current* GitHub head, which will
  not match `{{ .SHA }}` (and your local worktree/codegraph index) if upstream
  moved. If you detect such drift, note it in your verdict.
- Raise findings **only** on lines this PR introduced or changed. Pre-existing
  code is out of scope unless the diff changed its behavior.

### 2. Review round
{{ if ge .Round 2 -}}
This is **round {{ .Round }}** (a fix round). The prior rounds' review threads
